16th Annual Conference of the International Associotiation for World Englishes 
Short Title: IAWE 16 

Date: 25-Jul-2010 - 27-Jul-2010 
Location: Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada 
Contact: Suzanne K. Hilgendorf 
Contact Email: iawe2010@sfu.ca 
Meeting URL: http://www.iaweworks.org/conferences.php 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics; Sociolinguistics 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)

Meeting Description: 

The 16th Annual Conference of the International Association for World Englishes (IAWE 16) will be held July 25 - 27, 2010 at the Simon Fraser University Wosk Centre for Dialogue in Vancouver, Canada.

The conference theme is World Englishes Today: A Critical Reevaluation of Theory, Methodology, and Pedagogy in Global Contexts

Keynote Speakers:

Dr. Braj B. Kachru, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, USA (topic: English in Southeast Asia, theory of World Englishes)
Dr. Sue Wright, University of Portsmouth, UK (topic: English in Europe)
Dr. Nkonko Kamwangamalu, Howard University, Washington, D.C., USA (topic: English in Africa)

Focus Lectures 
Dr. Yamuna Kachru, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, USA (focus: English in Southeast Asia, theory of World Englishes)
Dr. Murray Munro, Simon Fraser University, Burnaby, Canada (focus: L2 Applied Phonetics)
Dr. Elizabeth Martin, California State University, San Bernardino, USA (focus: World Englishes and Advertising; English in France)
Dr. Jamie Shinhee Lee, University of Michigan-Dearborn, USA (focus: World Englishes and the Media; English in Korea and Japan)

We are now in the process of creating the 2010 conference website and preparing the Call for Papers, both of which we expect to have available in the first half of December. Access to the 2010 conference website and the CfP will be available via a link from the IAWE official website:

(http://www.iaweworks.org/conferences.php). 

Please check that site mid-December 2009 for further information. 







